ui/                           # 🌐 Streamlit UI
│
├── app.py                    # Main Streamlit app
├── config.py                 # Optional: UI config (API baseURL, theming, etc.)
├── utils.py                  # Helper functions (API calls, formatting)
├── components/               # Custom Streamlit components
│   ├── charts.py             # Charting / metric visualizations
│   ├── cards.py              # UI cards for predictions, model info
│   └── tables.py             # Tables for displaying data
├── assets/                   # Static assets
│   ├── logo.png
│   ├── favicon.ico
│   └── styles.css            # Optional custom CSS
├── pages/                    # Optional multipage Streamlit UI
│   ├── dashboard.py          # Metrics / ensemble visualization
│   └── history.py            # Historical predictions / logs
└── data/                     # Optional local cache
    └── predictions_cache.csv # Local cache of past predictions






Perfect, this structure gives us full flexibility for a slick, interactive UI. Here’s the plan to fill it out and make it fully functional:

1️⃣ app.py – main entrypoint
Sidebar for navigation: Prediction | History | Model Info | Dataset Upload
Columns for:
URL input + batch upload
Prediction output with color-coded badge
Calls utils.py to interact with your FastAPI endpoints:
/api/v1/predict for predictions
/api/v1/model-info for metadata
Optional: expanders for feature contributions, raw API response, tooltips
2️⃣ config.py
API base URL (http://localhost:8000/api/v1)
Theme colors: legit_color, phishing_color, background, etc.
Any other UI-level configs like max batch size
3️⃣ utils.py
API calls: fetch prediction, fetch model info
Data formatting: convert API JSON to Pandas DataFrame for tables
Cache management: optional caching of historical predictions locally
4️⃣ components/
charts.py:
Class distribution (pie/bar)
Metrics visualization (F1, accuracy, precision, recall)
Optional probability gauge for each URL
cards.py:
Stylized cards showing:
Prediction result (Legit / Phishing)
Probability with colored badge
Model used & version
tables.py:
DataFrames displayed in Streamlit tables
Support filtering, sorting, exporting CSV
5️⃣ assets/
logo.png for the top bar or sidebar
favicon.ico for Streamlit browser tab
styles.css (optional) for custom cards, colors, fonts
6️⃣ pages/
dashboard.py:
Overview of recent predictions
Ensemble stats if multiple models exist
Charts for class distribution and model performance
history.py:
Table with past predictions (cached locally or pulled from API if you implement a DB)
Export button to CSV
7️⃣ data/
predictions_cache.csv:
Store past predictions for session persistence or offline access
Columns: URL, prediction, probability, timestamp
